Introduction

Obesity is a major global health issue that has effects on both physical and mental health. New research that looks at the elements that contribute to obesity and how to forecast the condition based on these factors is necessary because the prevalence of obesity is continually rising. This dataset contains information for estimating the prevalence of obesity in people from Mexico, Peru, and Colombia based on their physical characteristics and eating patterns. The records are labeled with the class variable NObesity (Obesity Level), which enables the data to be classified using the following values: Normal Weight, Insufficient Weight, Obesity Type I, Obesity Type II, Obesity Type III, and Overweight Level I and II.

Attribute Information

There are altogether 5110 entries and 12 columns.

Features

  1. Gender - male or female
  2. Age
  3. Weight(kg)
  4. Height(m)
  5. family_history_with_overweight
  6. FAVC: High Caloric Food intake
  7. FCVC : Vegetable intake
  8. NCP : Number of main meal intake
  9. CAEC : Snacking behavior
  10. SMOKE : Smoking
  11. CH2O : Daily water intake
  12. SCC : Daily monitor calories intake
  13. FAF : physical activity
  14. TUE : Tech usage (hrs)
  15. CALC : Alcohol intake
  16. MTRANS : Mode of transportations

Target Label

  1. NObeyesdad (Obesity Level)
  • Underweight Less than 18.5
  • Normal 18.5 to 24.9
  • Overweight 25.0 to 29.9
  • Obesity I 30.0 to 34.9
  • Obesity II 35.0 to 39.9
  • Obesity III Higher than 40

Original Source : https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/544/estimation+of+obesity+levels+based+on+eating+habits+and+physical+condition

Problem Statement /Objective

I worked at a Start-up company and I have been assigned to create a mechine learning model to predict the possibilities of obesities level based on known data ( level data) by inputing the physical attributies and nutritation intake. So, that my company can build the app to predict the customers/patients' possibilites of the becoming obeses. This will help customers/patients to have preventation/ diet on early stages or take the medication/treatment plan immediately.

This model will be use 'Accuracy' as the primary tool to evaluate the model.

Final Discussion

As 3 different models have been implemented and by comparing results by far Logistic Regression is with the lowest accuracy rate with 88%. The remaining other 2 models ( SVM and Decision tree)' accuracy are quite simliar with the 93% and 92% respectivitely. Despite the simliar accuray, I would recommed to use the SVM model because as per F1_score the SVM perform better in class 5 and 6 compared to the other models.
